# --- Groq API — server-side only, used by /api/whisper-transcribe.js ---
# Deliberately NOT prefixed with VITE_: any VITE_* variable gets bundled
# into the client-side JS and would expose this key publicly in the
# browser. Vercel serverless functions (anything under /api) read
# unprefixed process.env vars, keeping this key server-side.
#
# Get a key at https://console.groq.com
# Set this in Vercel: Project Settings -> Environment Variables.
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# --- Vercel Blob — required for audio upload before transcription ---
# Audio is uploaded directly from the browser to Vercel Blob storage
# (bypassing the serverless function body-size limit), then fetched
# server-side and forwarded to Groq. To enable this:
#   1. In your Vercel project: Storage tab -> Create Database -> Blob
#   2. Connect it to this project
#   3. Vercel automatically injects BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN into your
#      deployment's environment — you do NOT need to set it manually here
#      in production. It's listed below only so local `vercel dev` picks
#      it up if you pull env vars with `vercel env pull`.
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# For local development you'd need `vercel dev` (not plain `vite dev`) for
# /api routes to run at all.
